services/alarmService.ts           - Alarm scheduling logic
services/notificationService.ts    - Enhanced for alarms
utils/sleepCycleCalculator.ts      - Wake window calculation
Key features:
Time picker (use your design's 07:30 style)
Smart window toggle (wake 0-30min early during light sleep)
Days of week selection (M T W T F S S pills)
Alarm sound picker
Vibration settings
Snooze configuration
Volume fade-in slider
Backup alarm toggle
2. Sleep Tracking Service Enhancement Enhance:
contexts/SleepContext.tsx
services/sleepTrackingService.ts
Add:
Accelerometer data collection
Sleep stage classification (basic algorithm)
Movement counting (restlessness)
Time to fall asleep calculation
Wake-up detection
Efficiency calculation (time asleep / time in bed)
3. Sleep Score Algorithm Create:
utils/sleepScoreCalculator.ts
Formula (based on your 82 score in designs):
sleepScore = (
  durationScore(25 points) +     // 7-9 hrs = full points
  qualityScore(25 points) +       // Efficiency % + wake-ups
  deepSleepScore(20 points) +     // 15-25% deep = full points
  remSleepScore(15 points) +      // 20-25% REM = full points  
  consistencyScore(15 points)     // Bedtime variation
) = Total /100
4. Update Existing Screens with Real Data Update these screens to use real calculated data:
HomeScreen.tsx - Real sleep score, deep/REM data
JournalScreen.tsx - Add hypnogram, stages chart
TrackerScreen.tsx - Connect to trends service
ğŸ“Š Data Structure Additions Needed
Your current sleep records need these new fields:
interface SleepRecord {
  // Existing fields...
  id: string;
  user_id: string;
  start_time: string;
  end_time: string;
  duration: number;
  
  // ADD THESE NEW FIELDS:
  sleep_score: number;                    // 0-100
  sleep_quality: 'poor' | 'fair' | 'good' | 'excellent';
  
  // Sleep stages (in minutes)
  awake_duration: number;
  light_sleep_duration: number;
  deep_sleep_duration: number;
  rem_sleep_duration: number;
  
  // Metrics
  time_to_fall_asleep: number;           // latency in minutes
  wake_count: number;                    // number of wake-ups
  efficiency_percent: number;             // (time asleep / time in bed) * 100
  restlessness_score: number;            // 0-100 movement count
  
  // Stage timeline (for hypnogram)
  sleep_stages: Array<{
    timestamp: string;
    stage: 'awake' | 'light' | 'deep' | 'rem';
    duration: number;
  }>;
  
  // Disruptions
  disruptions: Array<{
    timestamp: string;
    type: 'noise' | 'movement' | 'wake';
    severity: number;
    details?: string;
  }>;
  
  // Morning data
  morning_mood: 'terrible' | 'tired' | 'okay' | 'refreshed' | 'energized';
  morning_notes: string;
  
  // Lifestyle factors (for correlations)
  tags: string[];                         // ['exercise', 'caffeine', 'alcohol', etc]
  caffeine_intake: number;                // cups
  exercise_minutes: number;
  stress_level: number;                   // 1-10
  
  // Alarm data
  alarm_set: boolean;
  alarm_time: string;
  alarm_snoozed_count: number;
  actual_wake_time: string;
}
Update your Supabase schema to include these columns.
